  "prompt": "Can you give me some tips for getting rid of my internet addiction?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help reduce internet addiction:\n\n1. Set specific time limits for internet use\n- Use apps or device settings to track and limit screen time\n- Create \"no-phone zones\" like during meals or before bedtime\n\n2. Find alternative activities\n- Exercise\n- Read books\n- Practice a hobby\n- Spend time with friends and family in person\n- Engage in outdoor activities\n\n3. Create a structured daily routine\n- Schedule specific times for internet use\n- Plan offline activities\n- Use a planner or calendar\n\n4. Practice mindfulness\n- Meditation\n- Deep breathing exercises\n- Yoga\n- Journaling\n\n5. Remove digital temptations\n- Delete social media apps from your phone\n- Use website blockers\n- Keep devices out of your bedroom\n- Turn off notifications\n\n6. Gradually reduce internet time\n- Start with small, achievable reductions\n- Track your progress\n- Reward yourself for meeting goals\n\n7. Seek professional help\n- Counseling\n- Support groups\n- Addiction therapists\n\n8. Address underlying issues\n- Identify triggers for excessive internet use\n- Work on stress management\n- Improve self-esteem and social skills\n\nRemember, change takes time and patience. Be kind to yourself during the process.",
